<item>
            <title>[LU-13510] Allow control over LND timeouts independent of lnet_transaction_timeout and retry_count</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13510</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The commit &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/32770&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/32770&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9120&quot; title=&quot;LNet Network Health Feature&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9120&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-9120&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; lnet: calculate the lnd timeout&quot;) made it so the LND timeouts for ko2iblnd and ksocknal are derived from the lnet_transaction_timeout and retry_count. Thus, they can no longer be set independently. We should restore the ability to set these timeouts via their respective parameters (ko2iblnd timeout; ksocklnd sock_timeout).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="59024">LU-13510</key>
